# Candlestick Patterns
Candlestick patterns are divided into bearish and bullish.
Bullish - The price is likely to rise
Bearish - The price is likely to fall
Candlesticks are used to gauge the emotions surrounding an asset and can help predict trends.
![Pasted image 20220928123535.png](data:image/png;base64,)


### Bearish Engulfing Pattern
![Pasted image 20220928092206.png](data:image/png;base64,)

This indicates more people people are selling the stock and the price will **decline**

### Bullish Engulfing Pattern
![Pasted image 20220928092243.png](data:image/png;base64,)
Bullish engulfing pattern
Price is likely to increase 

### Bearish Evening Star
![Pasted image 20220928092414.png](data:image/png;base64,)
Stalling of buyers and the sellers taking control of the stock
More selling could develop  decrease in price


### Bearish Harami
![Pasted image 20220928092616.png](data:image/png;base64,)
This shows buyer indecision. It does not necessarily mean the price will increase or decrease, but should be observed. 

### Bullish Harami
![Pasted image 20220928093832.png](data:image/png;base64,)
Opposite of a [[Extracurricular/Stocks/Candlestick Patterns#Bearish Harami|Bearish Harami]], trend is pausing


### Bearing Harami Cross
![Pasted image 20220928093927.png](data:image/png;base64,)
A doji is an equal open and close. It occurs in an uptrend. 

### Bullish Rising Three
![Pasted image 20220928094020.png](data:image/png;base64,)
This starts out on a "long white day". Even through the price is fluctuating, it is not going beyond day 1 or day 5. It means that you should invest


### Bearish Falling Three
![Pasted image 20220928094133.png](data:image/png;base64,)
Pattern starts on a strong down day. It tells us sellers are in control and the price might decline.
